    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "\"FLYING OBJECTS IN GUAM: Unidentified flying objects have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "been observed by three American enlisted men of the 147th Air-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "ways and Air Communications Service Squadron at Harmon Field,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Guam. The men report that at 1040 hours on 14 August 1947 the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "two objects, which they describe as small, crescent shaped and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "traveling at a speed twice that of a fighter plane, passed over",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "them on a zig-zag course in a westerly direction at an approxi-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "mate altitude of twelve hundred feet. The objects disappeared",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "into clouds and a few seconds later a similar object possibly",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "one of those previously observed, emerged from the clouds and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "proceeded west. No further details have been reported.\"",
